## Content Wrapper Spacing

Progressive spacing based on breakpoints:

- **Mobile**: Compact spacing (`gap-2`, `p-4`)
- **Tablet**: Moderate spacing (`gap-3`, `p-4` in cards)
- **Desktop**: Comfortable spacing (`gap-4 lg:gap-7`, `p-4 md:p-5 lg:p-7` in cards)

Title sizes:
- Mobile: `text-3xl`
- Tablet: `text-2xl`
- Desktop: `text-2xl lg:text-3xl`

## Tailwind Responsive Classes

Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes consistently:
- `sm:` (640px and up)
- `md:` (768px and up) - Tablet breakpoint
- `lg:` (1024px and up) - Desktop breakpoint
- `xl:` (1280px and up)
- `2xl:` (1536px and up)

Example:
```tsx
<div className="p-2 md:p-4 lg:p-6">
  {/* Progressive padding: mobile → tablet → desktop */}
</div>
```

## Images and Assets

Ensure images and assets are optimized for different screen sizes:
